How to choose the mattress and bed base: women and men look for different things
Nothing pompous frame for the bed; what really confers its quality to a good bed is the surface to lie down, i.e. the mattress and the bed base.
First of all, they must be perfectly complemented so that they adapt to specific users.
During the election numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, state of health and sex of the owner.
Also important is the type of interior in which the mattress and the mattress pad are placed.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cottage that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they "warm up" more slowly.
In addition, they usually weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them around more frequently.
If the channels in the center are not properly ventilated and, above, are on a firm base, they keep moisture inside.
When choosing a bed, habits also influence.
Anyone who has spent a lot of time abroad often uses a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling good on a lower, harder surface.
“Almost every hockey player who came back from the NHL complained that they didn’t sleep as well here.”
"For their crushed shoulders, heels and hips they needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastic."
"This type of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes who time problems with the nervous system, so they receive poor information from the joints and skin," explains Sylva Hadamczikov<0xC3><0xA1>, who specializes in padded furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italian Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You no longer have to be an NHL player to appreciate viscoelasticity.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not turn around like after a hard game.
He just sleeps better.
Viscoelastic also works as a protection against sores.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to its height the length of your feet, that is, between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example singles, it is recommended at least between 120 and 140 cm.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, a simple rule for calculating the width can be applied: when lying on your back, you should have your hands comfortably shrunk towards your elbows," advises engineer Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>, an expert from Cechu <0xC4><0x8D>aloun<0xC3><0xAD>k<0xC5><0xAF> a dekoratér<0xC5><0xAF>, who has been dealing with the issue of healthy sleep and the ergonomics of furniture for many years, a subject she teaches.
In the double rooms, each one needs its own bed base and mattress, so during the purchase you have to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the bed bases at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with spring interior a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softens.
"By touching it with your hand or by accommodating on the mattress, the springs should certainly not be noticed," warns Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>.
Each mattress requires a certain type of mattress.
The fully padded bedrooms, in which the mattress and base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
Mattresses breathe badly and you can not wash their cover, which is often done today.
And, since every night we perspire between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a mattress life of up to 25 years or even a lifetime warranty.
However, everything has a but.
That's why sellers give a tip: on mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, take care of cleaning and washing the cover carefully, but better add a mattress protector that can be easily removed and washed.
Although mattress covers with a zipper closure are currently manufactured throughout their perimeter, so when they are opened they remain in two parts (something very important for washing and the size of the washing machine!), their handling in the larger models (and by one person) when lifting the mattress may seem like a fight between a fly weight and a heavy weight.
In bed, instead of a bed base, do you have a firm board?
Never! Never!
At most for the beds designed to spend one night the visits.
However, you should make (if you do not already have them) ventilation holes in the table and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with the springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non-articulable sheet bed bases containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g. a combination of latex and coconut fiber) may be used, although a bed base with a greater number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the lumbar area sheets are reinforced and their stiffness can be regulated is always best.
Articulable sheet bed bases should not be used with a spring mattress, as it does not react to recline.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the blades, shoulder protection can also be used.
It is a special fixation of the sheets that allows you to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they "surround" perfectly to the shoulders during sleep.
For men who have very broad shoulders, this is something very important.
They are even remembered by mattress manufacturers who, in the "male", began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are cross-frame or slatted bed bases with so-called multi-torsion damping.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the tension is lowered.
You should also keep in mind that even if you use the right mattress and pillowcase, if you use a bad pillow (large and "soft"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow should support the head and the corners can only reach the shoulders, so that the muscles of them can be relaxed.
The recommended suitable size is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying on your side, the pillow should be at the same level (when combined with the shoulder pad or the softer area of the mattress) as the shoulder height.
Modern mattresses seem to have something to do with original straw-filled mattresses.
Manufacturers continue to use, more and more often, natural materials or at least mixtures.
In fact, biological mattresses are fashionable.
Petroleum-based raw materials, from which polyurethane foam is made, are filled with natural oils, for example castor or soybean.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soybeans.
“Biologic, in the case of mattresses, means that the center is made only of materials of natural origin,” explains Petr Va<0xC5><0xA1><0xC3><0xAD><0xC4><0x8D>ek of the company Tropico Plus.
Also, natural substances are used during the manufacture of the mattress cover, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for microcapsules, which release a fresh aroma to forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men "refresh" themselves with plant extracts from the breeze, so that the mattress cover absorbs heat and cools the body, women prefer to "heat" the cover.
Red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so that women feel warmer.
Favorites currently?
Mattresses made of cold foam, which are more porous, with an adapted cell structure, which makes them more permeable than normal polyurethane and offer more permeability.
The combination of various cold and viscoelastic foam rigidities allows mattresses to be manufactured from different areas that know perfectly where the head, shoulders and heels go.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand crowns up.
Those who play a therapeutic role usually have a lower VAT, since they are considered as health means.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It is difficult to save on mattresses and bed bases.
Sometimes you can approve offers from manufacturers or sellers, who sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with a memory foam attached to the case for 11,990 crowns.
The second one is available for free.
The era of viscoelastic with an open cell structure and high density began with Tempur's "cosmic" material.
Initially it emerged as material for NASA, because during the takeoffs the astronauts were subjected to a huge overload.
Tempur softens with heat and hardens with cold.
Therefore, the warm human body exerts a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores, but also to improve comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foam is not only used in mattresses, but also for sanitary products, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
Domestic manufacturers, for example, use Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and the like.
More and more parents are using people tracking devices to control their children
The fear of children leads more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle tracking, can also track the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, in the case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old girl Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka Janatkov<0xC3><0xA1>.
At the moment the device has the approximate size of a match box, but it will soon be reduced to the size of a clock.
Many people were frightened by the case of the missing Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka and began to report on the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
“We’re all trying to tell ourselves that it’s not about spying, but another means to lessen the chances of a tragedy,” says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
“I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they get into someone’s purse without their knowledge, but we have not yet come across such cases.”
“Most customers actually buy it for security reasons,” Pilin adds.
In his opinion, children should always know what the "box" is for and how it is used in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bo<0xC4><0x8D>kov<0xC3><0xA1> warns that if the child does not want to take it, he will simply throw it away.
“Even the youngest children show great creativity when it comes to intentionally losing certain things if they want to prevent them from being controlled.”
“Previously, parents relied heavily on mobile phones, but these could be turned off as easily as the tracking device,” says Bo<0xC4><0x8D>kov<0xC3><0xA1>.
In his opinion, it is questionable whether in case of attack such a device is really useful.
“If it is a prepared abduction, the perpetrator will almost always check if the child is carrying any type of electronic device that can reveal his location.”
"Now it's the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices expands, it will also search for them, since their sale will undoubtedly be done with a lot of publicity."
“In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police,” says the psychologist.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the case of an improvised attack by a pedophile.
According to Robert <0xC4><0x8C>ech of the company RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even in the event that, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can be of help.
"The device can be set to send the position regularly after a certain period of time."
“If it is damaged, it will at least facilitate the last position of the person in question.”
“The most expensive devices have an inclination meter built in, so if the person just slips and sits still, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question,” says <0xC4><0x8C>ech.
In his opinion, such a service can be obtained even with smart phones with navigation, in which only special software must be installed.
The problem with current tracking units is that at the moment they are devices with a similar size to a matchbox or smaller mobile phones.
Therefore, they can be lost.
According to Pilin de Macro Weil, for that reason, tests are currently being carried out with devices that look like a digital clock.
“In addition, they will have the added advantage that a potential aggressor may not identify the device.”
“Or to identify him after a certain time, which can save the police time,” he adds.
Even if the tracking devices are worn on the wrist or hanging, they will continue to use the same technology that is used for vehicle tracking.
This is the verification of the position with a GPS system (which is used in the usual navigation in the car) combined with the function of a mobile phone that communicates the current position.
The army has enough wicks to encircle the whole Czech Republic, but they only last two years.
The Czech army bought 445 kilometers of wick to set off explosives.
Last year, the Ministry of Defense added 224 kilometers of wick to its arsenal.
Therefore, they have stocks for 225 years.
The problem is that the life of the wick is two years, four at most.
The army bought the wick for explosives from the STV Group, a.s. for forty million crowns.
The General’s staff responded to MF DNES justifying the purchase of such a huge amount of wick by saying that soldiers need for training maneuvers 60 kilometers of wick per year.
According to the calculations of the fireworks technicians of the army, with whom MF DNES was contacted, it is decided, however, that, in such a case, should perform such maneuvers with frequent use of explosives every year also all generals, high-ranking officers, and even secretaries and cleaners.
Neither Defense Minister Alexandr Vondr and Army Captain Vlastimil Picek wanted exemptions.
Only in this way could the army be justified in spending sixty kilometers of wick.
Such a length is equivalent to 25,000 explosions.
Even if that were the case, the army would have sufficient stockpiles for more than ten years.
If on the contrary, as experts say, for the initial training of each new professional comes with a maximum of two meters of wick, the army would have with the new purchase (including adding the consumption of the units of engineers or special) sufficient stock for the 225 indicated above.
The soldiers of the rapid intervention brigade complained personally recently to Minister Vondra because they say they have scarce ammunition for various weapons, so that even the practice of firing for a matter of money is limited.
And let's not talk about the lack of underwear.
"I also don't understand that we repeatedly buy such quantities of wick."
“But it’s their decision, and they’ll certainly know why they act like that.”
